example-name: Tag suggestions
example-description: Suggest tags based on content and existing wiki taxonomy (injected via system prompt)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

!! Tag suggestions

The wiki's tag taxonomy is injected via `inject-as: system-prompt`, so the LLM has persistent awareness of existing tags. The tiddler content goes as the user message (built-in default). Result written to `field:suggested-tags`.

''Settings covered:'' action mode, `output-mode: text`, `output-target: field:suggested-tags`, `inject-as: system-prompt`, prompt template precedence

```
<$button>
  Suggest tags
  <$llm-action
    tiddler=<<currentTiddler>>
    promptTemplate="$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/prompts/tag-suggestions"
  />
</$button>
```

!!! Live demo

<$button>
  Suggest tags
  <$llm-action
